{
  "doc_id": "32103",
  "text": "In a series by Frédéric Bert et al. [CITATION_1] , signs of shock were present in only 4 out of the 51 patients with S. milleri bacteremia, with only 2 deaths out of these 51 patients. The mortality rates of bacteremic patients have been variable, and has been quoted as 12.5% in one series by Casariego et al [CITATION_2] , to as high as 26% in another series by Jacobs et al, though this was mainly among severely ill patients [CITATION_3] .",
